    <p class="blog-content">The Western Disturbance is a meteorological phenomenon that affects the weather patterns of the Indian subcontinent and neighboring regions. It is a low-pressure system that originates in the Mediterranean region and moves eastwards, affecting the weather in India, Pakistan, and other neighboring countries. The Western Disturbance has been the subject of extensive research in recent years due to its impact on various weather patterns, including winter rainfall, monsoon rains, and snowfall in the Himalayan region.</p>
